      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Add local-realtime-voice extension (gateway-relay realtime voice/dictation)",
        "body": "This PR adds a free, self-hosted realtime voice and dictation provider for OpenClaw over the `gateway-relay` transport.\n\n**What it does**\n- Registers a realtime voice provider (`local`) using Whisper STT, Ollama chat, and Kokoro TTS.\n- Registers a realtime transcription provider (`local`) for dictation.\n- Supports both `g711_ulaw_8kHz` and `pcm16_24kHz` audio formats over the gateway-relay transport.\n- Emits rolling partial transcripts for dictation and chunks assistant TTS audio for low-latency playback.\n- Requires no paid API keys; runs on local Docker containers.\n\n**Clients**\n- This is a client-agnostic gateway-relay provider. It is not Android-specific.\n- It has been tested end-to-end with the OpenClaw Android Companion app over Tailscale (`talk.session.create`).\n- Any other OpenClaw client using the same realtime relay path (iOS, web, desktop) can use it once configured.\n\n**Files added**\n- `extensions/local-realtime-voice/index.js`\n- `extensions/local-realtime-voice/openclaw.plugin.json`\n- `extensions/local-realtime-voice/package.json`\n- `extensions/local-realtime-voice/README.md`\n- `extensions/local-realtime-voice/LICENSE`\n\n**Notes**\n- The extension is intentionally authored in plain JavaScript to keep the initial contribution simple; happy to port to TypeScript if maintainers prefer.\n- Default endpoints assume local Docker services (`faster-whisper-server`, `kokoro-fastapi-cpu`, and Ollama).\n- Companion npm package is prepared as `openclaw-local-realtime-voice` for users who prefer installing outside the monorepo.\n\nCloses the gap for users who want local Android/Companion voice without OpenAI or Google Cloud billing.\n",
        "branch": "feat/local-realtime-voice",
